5000|$|On February 17, 2015, Astorino {{announced}} he would {{change the name of}} the party to the [...] "Reform Party" [...] to broaden its appeal beyond a single issue. The party initially ran into opposition from the Conservative Party of New York State, who balked at allowing another ballot line to cross-endorse its candidates. Marie Smith became the chairperson of the state's newly created/balloted Reform Party.Marie Smith stepped down as Chairperson, and Bill C. Merrell, Ph.D. was elected NYS Chair on January 12, 2016.The NYS <b>Reform</b> <b>Party</b> as authorized by <b>the</b> National <b>Reform</b> <b>Party</b> is in full support with Bill C. Merrell, Ph.D., as Chairman of <b>the</b> National <b>Reform</b> <b>Party</b> and <b>the</b> NYS <b>Reform</b> <b>Party.</b> <b>The</b> NYS <b>Reform</b> <b>party</b> (Nationally Affiliated) has added its opposition to common core to its web site and values page. The current party may win or lose the appeal, however without National approval, <b>the</b> name <b>REFORM</b> <b>PARTY</b> is owned and is {{under the control of the}} National Executive Committee of <b>the</b> (National) <b>Reform</b> <b>Party,</b> www.reformparty.com which Bill C. Merrell, Ph.D. serves as National Chair of from 2017 to 2020. [...] "At the very least the renegade group who is temporarily using our name without permission is at least not using our logo." [...] stated Merrell. Anyone who wants a real/legal and legitimate endorsement from the Nationally Approved New York State <b>Reform</b> <b>Party</b> must contact Bill Merrell, State Chair, of <b>the</b> Nationally affiliated <b>Reform</b> <b>Party.</b> Bill Merrell, Ph.D. also serves as the National Chair of <b>the</b> (National) <b>Reform</b> <b>Party</b> www.reformparty.com.|$|R
